    "client_msg_id": "049adc03-06c4-496c-ae75-ddd508fd19f3",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I'm currently working on a set of simple tools to make data from the apple products available on the traditional web.\n\n• <https://montaigne.io> - create website from apple notes\n• <https://public.photos> - publish photos online from apple photos. a bit on pause\n• <https://kiwi.page> - publish apple notes online. a bit on pause too\nThere are few interesting moments here for me:\n\n1. liberate data from apple products\n2. explore idea of <https://www.inkandswitch.com/local-first/|local first software> but in a different way. what is cool with this approach that data lives locally on your devices and then I just sync it to the web where it can be viewed and used by everyone\n\nIt's not super challenging programming wise, but interesting to think about in terms of how software can be written",
